The paper proposes a method for ear identification using image processing techniques and machine learning algorithms. The use of SIFT features and Gaussian mixture models suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The application of K-L divergence and the use of fusion approaches indicate that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms and the evaluation of accuracy suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
